<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861210-0118 </DOCNO><HL> Doubleday Holders ClearFirm's Sale to Bertelsmann</HL><DD> 12/10/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PUBLISHING (PUB) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Doubleday andamp; Co. said shareholders approved at a special meeting yesterday the sale of the company to Bertelsmann AG.    The West German communications concern plans to buy the publisher for about $500 million. Holders also approved the sale of the company's 95% interest in Doubleday Sports, the unit that operates the New York Mets baseball team, to a company formed by Nelson Doubleday and Fred Wilpon. The unit is to be sold for $80.75 million. </TEXT></DOC>